4CHPROR3 supports [RF remotes](sonoff_RM433) independent from Tasmota, it is managed by a secondary MCU.

If you want to use the RF433 module, direct connect SYN470R output to SDA (GPIO2) and configure [RF Receiver](https://tasmota.github.io/docs/RF-Protocol/#receiving-rf-codes).
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3578202/139196247-4f67058f-3f2f-4d8e-81e7-f08dfc9595bb.jpg)

